column1: #Text=Tecate is a small city in Baja California ( state ) on the border with California , about an hour east of Tijuana .
#Text=Unlike most US/Mexico border crossings , there is no town on the US side .
#Text=Take the toll road ( " cuota " ) that parallels Mexico Highway 2 , 30 miles east .
#Text=Highway 2 then leads east about 80 miles to Mexicali by way of the notorious " Rumorosa Grade " .

column1: #Text=The highway is two lanes and is about a 75 minute drive to the border crossing .
#Text=Tecate 's border crossing is probably the easiest in California .
#Text=You can pay a few dollars to park at one of the lots on the US side and walk across the border .
#Text=It can also be an alternative border crossing to get back into the US ; it 's less crowded than the San Ysidro and Otay Mesa border crossings ( to get back into the US ) .
#Text=It will be a long drive from Tijuana , but it will save you some time .
#Text=The Golden Door is another Spa that was later established by Deborah Szekely , a co-founder of Rancho La Puerta .
#Text=California Motorsport Adventours Based in San Diego .
#Text=Off road adventure tours for people of all riding abilities .
#Text=Everyone welcome : families , couples , friends , single riders , bachelor and corporate groups .
#Text=Full day excursions or longer tours available also .
#Text=Ride in the dunes and then enjoy a guided adventure into the surrounding mountain trails .
#Text=Our trips out to Tecate are 2 to 4 days long .
#Text=Contact the office for reservations and inquiries .
#Text=Tecate has a central shopping plaza , but those crossing the border and looking for souvenirs will be disappointed .
#Text=Tecate is home to the namesake Tecate Brewery , which offers tours .
#Text=A small ranch hotel south of Tecate that also offers a range out outdoor experiences .
#Text=The Vinicola L.A. Cetto winery , along Highway 3 , offers tours .

#Text=Guadelupe Canyon hot springs , with nearby hiking and petroglyphs , is located 30 miles down a dirt road east of La Rumorosa .
